Complaint One: We need a cute flight log notebook. Black is too boring, and pink is not pink at all—it's salmon red.
I've always wanted to fly.
Today's dream has come true... I actually flew the plane today. I'm still not back to reality yet.
data from FlightAware
I plan to try again on Saturday. The weather doesn't look good today, but it's only Monday.
It seems the challenges in this area are already starting to show. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it requires a lot of time and involves a lot of extra work.
Although it's a bit frustrating, this is just another problem that needs to be solved, and it seems "definitely" solvable at the moment. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'm going to face next:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
