Flying is very physically demanding. My back and legs are aching badly today, feeling as if I had gone to the gym.
This is not as simple as taking a drive on Sunday. In my inexperienced eyes, it's more like a sport than a cruise.
Dear friends, happy Saturday. Welcome to 4,000 feet in the air.
I will fly again tomorrow, and we will practice stalls and slow flight.
The weather was unstable today but super fun. We practiced slow flight and stalls. Our ground speed dropped as low as 16 miles per hour, while our airspeed remained at 65 miles per hour.
The weather was clear today, and although there was some mist at high altitude, the view was still great.
